Fordgobike Slide Deck¶

This document explores a dataset describing fordgobike which is a regional public bicycle sharing system in San Francisco

Gender Distribution in Dataset¶

duration with gender¶

It seems that All genders have nearly the same duration distribution But The median value for female is slightly higher than male and other¶

duration with user_type¶

It is clear the on average customers have longer trips than subscribers¶

start_day with trip duraiion for each gender¶

It seems that Males and females tend to have lower trips on weekends¶

start_day with trip duraiion for each user_type¶

It seems that Subscriber users also have lower trips on week ends But for Customer users all days tend to be the same¶

start_hour with trip duraiion for each gender_type¶

It seems that also that Males and females have top number of trips at 17 and 8 hours due to work hours¶

start_hour with trip duraiion for each user_type¶

It seems that also that Subscriber users also have top number of trips at 17 and 8 hours due to work hours. But customer users slightly difference in most hours except from 23 to 6 the trips are very rare¶

Trip duration with member_gender¶

It seems that females have trip duration more than males¶

Trip duration with user_type¶

It seems that Customers have trip duration more than Subscribers¶

Age with duration for each day¶

It seems ages around from 20 to 40 years who are at working age have most of trips¶
